b"Another tough workout this week with @spartan Champ @robert_killian. Check out his official Instagram account to watch the full videos!
\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb
This week\xe2\x80\x99s @USAA At-Home Grit Together is a beast! Featuring exercises you can do from home to work on speed, threshold, and core strength. The current focus in the Army, fitness-wise, is preparing for the ACFT. I'm a stickler on hard work with a specialty on the basics, therefore let's keep it simple but challenging. I'm excited to get back to racing and hitting the @Spartan Honor Series when we\xe2\x80\x99re back in action!
------
Today we be working to improve threshold heart rate for the 2 mile run, event 6 of the ACFT. Get after it anytime this weekend!\xc2\xa0Make sure you practice situational awareness when exercising outdoors or using modified equipment.
------
Workout: 30 min EMOM; There are 5 stations to rotate through. You can do them in any order you choose; going non stop will get you 6 total rounds. (begin the next exercise immediately at the start of every minute on the minute)
.
- Sprint: 200m run, 15 kcal Stationary Bike or 45 seconds
.
- Dips: 20 reps
.
- Weighted Burpees: 10 reps with ~30% Bodyweight
.
- Sprint: 200m run, Row for 220m, or Stationary Bike again
.
- Weighted Lunges: 15 knee taps total ~40% Bodyweight
------
#killianit #grittogether #usaa #honorseries #racewithhonor #USAAPartner #spartan #spartanrace #spartanpro #stayhomeworkout"

This week\xe2\x80\x99s @USAA At-Home Grit Together features exercises you can do from home to focus on speed, threshold, and core strength. The current focus in the Army, fitness-wise, is preparing for the ACFT. I'm a stickler on hard work with a focus on the basics, therefore let's keep it simple but challenging. I'm excited to get back to racing and hitting the @Spartan Honor Series when we\xe2\x80\x99re back in action!
------
Today we'll hit the Sprint-Drag-Carry, event 4 of the ACFT. Get after it anytime this weekend!\xc2\xa0Make sure you practice situational awareness when exercising outdoors or using modified equipment.
------
Workout: 30 min AMRAP; 1 Round is all the below exercises (begin the next exercise immediately after the other)
.
- Suicide Sprints: Go to the 10m then 25m and back
.
- Sled Drag: Reverse pull 50m; 90lbs minimum
.
- Lateral Shuffle: 25m right leg lead - 25m back left leg lead
.
- Farmer Carry Sprint: 50m with 40lbs in each hand minimum
.
- Sprint: 50m
.
- Medicine Ball Crunch Toss: 10 reps; 20-30lbs
.
- Russian Kettlebell Twist: 20 taps total (10 each side) 20-30lbs
------
Let me know how many rounds you grit out!
------

\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb
This week\xe2\x80\x99s @USAA At-Home Grit Together features exercises you can do from home to focus on grip, core, and leg strength. The current focus in the Army, fitness-wise, is preparing for the ACFT. I'm a stickler on hard work with a focus on the basics. I'm excited to get back to racing and hitting the @Spartan Honor Series when we\xe2\x80\x99re back in action!
------
Today's focus is on the leg tuck exercises, event 5 of the ACFT. Get after it anytime this weekend!
------
Workout:
- Crunch: 20, 15, 10 ,5 reps with 30 seconds rest between and 1 minute rest before going back up 5, 10, 15, 20.
.
- Sandbag Carry: 60-90lbs 100m x 3 sets or Weighted Lunges x 15 knee to ground x 3 sets with 2 min rest between
.
- Side Plank: 30 second holds each side x 3 sets and 30 seconds rest between sets - Russian Twist: 20 taps total x 3 sets 1 min rest between sets
.
- Dead Hang: (opposing grip) 1 min on 1 min off, 45 seconds on 45 off, 30 on 30 off, 15 on 15 off. *supplemental add a 15lb weight vest
.
- Push Squat: 15 reps x 3 sets 1 min rest between sets.
------
#killianit #grittogether #usaa #honorseries #racewithhonor #USAAPartner #spartan #spartanrace #spartanpro #stayhomeworkout"
